## The agent loop is sacred

The four phases — extract, retrieve, score, decide — are the product. Get them right above all else.

- `extract` calls Anthropic with structured tool-use. Real API. Real `claude-opus-4-7`.
- `retrieve` is pure in-memory string similarity. No LLM. No external API (unless Specter is wired in late).
- `score` is a pure function. No randomness. No LLM. Deterministic given inputs.
- `decide` is a pure function. Threshold check. Returns `'PAY' | 'REFUSE'`.

If you're tempted to "make this more interesting" by adding LLM calls in `score` or `decide`, **don't**. The whole pitch rests on these being deterministic and auditable. The LLM stochasticity is bounded to extraction.

## The receipt is sacred

Every receipt must:
- Be signed before it leaves the agent loop
- Have a stable, canonicalisable JSON shape
- Round-trip through `signReceipt → verifyReceipt` returning `true`
- Round-trip through `signReceipt → tamper any byte → verifyReceipt` returning `false`

Test these invariants once when the spine is built. If they don't hold, stop and fix. Everything downstream depends on them.

## Decision-making summary

When in doubt: **does it serve the 90-second demo?** If yes, do it. If no, skip it.
